## One Important AI-Generated Terraform Issue I'd Flag

Many AI-generated examples grant:

```terraform
roles/editor
```

or

```terraform
roles/owner
```

to deployment service accounts because it "just works."

For a healthcare workload with PHI-bordering data, this violates least-privilege and typically fails security review. I deliberately used scoped roles (`container.admin`, `cloudsql.client`, `logWriter`, etc.) and would verify them against Flowvelly's IAM matrix before implementation rather than assuming broad access.
